abstract_ssm: Pamela Sporn is a documentary filmmaker whose films combine personal narratives and archival materials to tell stories about working-class life. The Pamela Sporn papers contain videos and research materials related to Sporn's documentaries. The bulk of the collection and consists of approximately 400 digital video files as well as research files created by Sporn for her film A Humble Giant: 70 Years Defending Immigrants and Radicals, about immigration lawyer Ira Gollobin. It also includes DVDs of Sporn's documentaries With a Stroke of the Chevata and Disobeying Orders: GI Resistance to the Vietnam War, and analog video footage of interviews from With a Stroke of the Chevata and A Humble Giant.
